I moved better last summer
when a bee flew in my shorts.

37
00:02:39,995 --> 00:02:43,065
I'm waiting, "Preppie. "
Let's see what you got.

38
00:02:43,098 --> 00:02:47,469
Move back, give him room.
Hot feet coming through!

39
00:02:52,708 --> 00:02:56,211
Slater, I could beat you now with
three toes tied behind my back.

40
00:02:56,244 --> 00:02:59,147
<i>You think you're
a better dancer than me?</i>

41
00:02:59,181 --> 00:03:02,484
Go practice first,
then we'll have a real dance-off.

42
00:03:02,517 --> 00:03:06,288
Wow, a dancing duel.
How exciting!

43
00:03:10,292 --> 00:03:13,829
Hey Lisa, my horoscope says
we're destined to dance together.

44
00:03:13,862 --> 00:03:17,433
My horoscope says,
"Beware of dorks. "

45
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:21,303
Well, I'll protect you
from them!

46
00:03:22,905 --> 00:03:25,908
Hey Jessie, you want to be
my partner for the dance contest?

47
00:03:25,941 --> 00:03:28,544
Gee Danny, I'd love to.

48
00:03:29,545 --> 00:03:32,381
Actually, no. I don't believe
in dance contests.

49
00:03:32,414 --> 00:03:34,583
Then why don't we just
skip the contest and kiss all night?

50
00:03:34,617 --> 00:03:37,887
Bye, Danny.

51
00:03:38,988 --> 00:03:41,524
Hmm...

52
00:03:41,557 --> 00:03:44,260
skip the date and start
with a goodnight kiss?

53
00:03:44,293 --> 00:03:47,096
That Danny has good ideas.

54
00:03:49,131 --> 00:03:51,133
Jessie:
This cannot be right.

55
00:03:51,167 --> 00:03:54,570
Tell me something is wrong with
this scale before I hyperventilate.

56
00:03:54,603 --> 00:03:58,708
The only thing wrong with that scale
is the flake who's on it.

57
00:03:58,741 --> 00:04:03,145
I have grown an inch taller
since lunch. I feel like a giant.

58
00:04:03,179 --> 00:04:05,381
You are not a giant.

59
00:04:05,414 --> 00:04:07,883
You're a bright, sensitive,
popular girl.

60
00:04:07,917 --> 00:04:10,353
Everyone "looks up"
to you.

61
00:04:10,386 --> 00:04:12,622
Thanks a lot.

62
00:04:12,655 --> 00:04:15,491
I mean, what's going to happen to me
if I keep growing?

63
00:04:15,524 --> 00:04:17,527
Stand tall. Be proud.

64
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:20,763
And practice your slam dunk.

65
00:04:20,796 --> 00:04:24,133
Before I begin I have to make
a very sad announcement.

66
00:04:24,167 --> 00:04:27,303
Beethoven's alive?

67
00:04:27,336 --> 00:04:31,441
<i>Very amusing, Mr. Morris.
* Ha-ha ha-ha. *</i>

68
00:04:32,442 --> 00:04:35,678
No, unfortunately
I have to conduct

69
00:04:35,712 --> 00:04:38,948
two music classes today,
simultaneously.

70
00:04:38,981 --> 00:04:42,652
Poor Mrs. Wickham slipped
and got her head stuck in a tuba.

71
00:04:42,685 --> 00:04:46,456
Well maybe they should get
"Fat Tommy" to blow her out.

72
00:04:46,489 --> 00:04:48,491
Good suggestion.

73
00:04:48,524 --> 00:04:50,627
All right, people, today,
we're going to play a piece

74
00:04:50,660 --> 00:04:53,763
by Johann Sebastian Bach.

75
00:04:53,796 --> 00:04:55,798
A piece?

76
00:04:55,832 --> 00:04:57,834
Why can't we play
the whole thing?

77
00:04:57,867 --> 00:05:01,805
All right people, instruments up!
One bar for nothing.

78
00:05:01,838 --> 00:05:05,408
One, and two, and three,
and...

79
00:05:11,715 --> 00:05:14,384
Oh! Thrilling!

80
00:05:15,585 --> 00:05:18,221
Bach always gives me chills.

81
00:05:21,091 --> 00:05:23,426
<i>Keep playing my little
wunderkind,</i>

82
00:05:23,460 --> 00:05:27,063
<i>I'll be right Bach-
I mean, back.</i>

83
00:05:45,282 --> 00:05:49,419
Beautiful, beautiful!
I'm getting chills.

84
00:05:49,453 --> 00:05:52,055
Are you feeling
what I'm feeling?

85
00:05:52,089 --> 00:05:55,292
Yes sir, it was
the fish sticks at lunch.

86
00:05:55,325 --> 00:05:57,661
You are what you eat,
Powers.

87
00:05:57,694 --> 00:06:00,264
All right, let me hear
the horns!

88
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,136
No chewing gum in class,
Mr. Morris.

89
00:06:07,137 --> 00:06:09,239
All right, piano!

90
00:06:14,978 --> 00:06:18,348
Elegantly played, Powers.
Let's hear strings and flute!

91
00:06:21,051 --> 00:06:23,120
You're moving me,
you're moving me.

92
00:06:27,124 --> 00:06:29,293
Slater:
All right, move it, Jessie!

93
00:06:29,326 --> 00:06:31,462
Kelly:
Whoo! Shake it, girl!

94
00:06:39,570 --> 00:06:41,839
Zack, why don't you show Kelly
what a great dancer you are?

95
00:06:41,872 --> 00:06:44,108
Not now, Screech.

96
00:06:44,141 --> 00:06:46,544
Go ahead, Zack,
I'm dying to see you dance.

97
00:06:46,577 --> 00:06:49,780
Yeah, dazzle us,
Preppie.

98
00:06:55,252 --> 00:06:57,888
Wonderful. This is why
I went into teaching.

99
00:06:57,922 --> 00:07:00,891
Wonderful, wonderful.
Now a little faster tempo.

100
00:07:00,925 --> 00:07:03,627
<i>Allegro con molto.
Poco, poco. Yes.</i>

101
00:07:03,661 --> 00:07:06,397
<i>Nice. A little "brighter. "
Yes, nice.</i>

102
00:07:06,430 --> 00:07:09,000
