<i>* Let's twist again,
like we did last summer *</i>

142
00:09:30,209 --> 00:09:33,879
<i>* Yeah, let's twist again,
like we did last year. *</i>

143
00:09:38,317 --> 00:09:41,086
You want me to recreate
that moment, right?

144
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:45,391
Well actually, I was hoping
I could borrow a school banner.

145
00:09:45,424 --> 00:09:48,427
A banner?
That's all?

146
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:51,130
That's all, "Bopper. "

147
00:09:51,163 --> 00:09:54,433
Well okay, I'll present it
to you on the show.

148
00:09:54,466 --> 00:09:56,468
Gee, that'd be great.
But I can take it right now.

149
00:09:56,502 --> 00:09:59,338
I don't have one right now.

150
00:09:59,371 --> 00:10:01,373
I'll bring it to you.

151
00:10:03,409 --> 00:10:05,711
Oh, Zack, when are you
going to have the dance-off?

152
00:10:05,745 --> 00:10:07,847
I need to know
who my partner is.

153
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:10,616
Well, Slater will be humiliated
the day after tomorrow.

154
00:10:10,649 --> 00:10:12,985
Are you really
that much better than him?

155
00:10:13,019 --> 00:10:16,155
Every summer while the other kids
were playing baseball,

156
00:10:16,188 --> 00:10:18,190
I was at dance camp.

157
00:10:18,224 --> 00:10:20,760
Wow, I can't wait.

158
00:10:23,062 --> 00:10:26,332
Why did I say that?

159
00:10:31,904 --> 00:10:35,575
Zack:
Whatever you're doing, don't.

160
00:10:37,043 --> 00:10:40,747
My darling, be my partner,
and this could be you.

161
00:10:50,289 --> 00:10:52,225
So what do you say?
Pick you up, seven-ish?

162
00:10:52,258 --> 00:10:55,228
Forget it, Screech.
She's already going with me.

163
00:10:55,261 --> 00:10:57,263
Lisa, is that true?

164
00:10:57,297 --> 00:11:01,067
Sorry Screech, he asked me
this morning. Come on.

165
00:11:03,002 --> 00:11:06,239
It's all your fault.
I told you to let me lead.

166
00:11:12,479 --> 00:11:15,949
- Whoo! You're doing great.
- I am?

167
00:11:15,982 --> 00:11:18,685
Hey, I am, aren't I?

168
00:11:18,718 --> 00:11:21,621
Okay now, here's a new step
I just invented.

169
00:11:25,125 --> 00:11:28,094
- Awesome.
- Come on. Do it with me.

170
00:11:28,128 --> 00:11:30,430
Slater's going to freak out
when he sees this.

171
00:11:30,463 --> 00:11:32,465
Whoo!

172
00:11:38,305 --> 00:11:40,307
Let's take five.

173
00:11:40,340 --> 00:11:43,109
Yeah, let's cool down.
You're new at this.

174
00:11:48,515 --> 00:11:50,717
Thanks.

175
00:11:50,750 --> 00:11:52,853
You're a terrific dancer.

176
00:11:52,886 --> 00:11:55,622
Yeah, well, I went to dance camp
when I was a kid.

177
00:11:55,655 --> 00:11:58,158
They actually have those?

178
00:11:58,191 --> 00:12:01,795
I can't believe
you're not entering the contest.

179
00:12:01,828 --> 00:12:03,697
No big deal.

180
00:12:03,730 --> 00:12:05,632
You're not into some
strange religion, are you?

181
00:12:05,666 --> 00:12:08,602
- No.
- Then what's the problem?

182
00:12:08,635 --> 00:12:11,905
Zack, I don't want
to talk about it, okay?

183
00:12:14,808 --> 00:12:17,811
- Would you like to dance with me?
- I can't. I'm bigger than you.

184
00:12:17,844 --> 00:12:20,314
And I'm still growing
at this very moment.

185
00:12:24,284 --> 00:12:27,454
Too bad. Maybe I should have asked
10 minutes ago.

186
00:12:29,423 --> 00:12:31,425
Hey Jessie, let's dance.

187
00:12:35,429 --> 00:12:38,232
I'm too big for you.
I'm too big for everyone.

188
00:12:41,435 --> 00:12:45,139
- Jessie, is that you up there?
- Yes, it's me.

189
00:12:45,172 --> 00:12:47,641
You don't want
to dance with me, do you?

190
00:12:47,675 --> 00:12:50,511
I can't.
Everybody will laugh at us.

191
00:12:52,646 --> 00:12:56,083
Zack, I do have a problem-
I'm too tall.

192
00:12:56,116 --> 00:12:58,419
Well, I haven't noticed
anyone measuring you lately.

193
00:12:58,452 --> 00:13:01,021
That's because
they can't reach me.

194
00:13:01,055 --> 00:13:04,825
Zack, you don't know
what it's like to be "the freak"-

195
00:13:04,859 --> 00:13:08,262
taller than all the boys-
the jokes, the looks, the whispers.

196
00:13:08,295 --> 00:13:12,867
- Stop looking up at me!
- Look at the bright side.

197
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:15,569
At least you're the first one
to know when it rains.

198
00:13:15,603 --> 00:13:16,637
Zack!

199
00:13:16,670 --> 00:13:19,540
I'm sorry. Come on, there's
lots of guys taller than you.

200
00:13:19,573 --> 00:13:21,642
Name one.

201
00:13:21,676 --> 00:13:24,545
Kareem Abdul-Jabbar?

202
00:13:36,390 --> 00:13:39,627
Come on, Screech, cheer up.
It can't be that bad.

203
00:13:39,660 --> 00:13:44,132
It's no use trying
to look stud-like anymore.

204
00:13:44,165 --> 00:13:47,668
I think this time it's really over
between me and Lisa.

205
00:13:47,702 --> 00:13:49,704
Look, you can't give up.

206
00:13:49,737 --> 00:13:54,242
I heard if Byron hadn't asked Lisa
first, she'd have gone with you.

207
00:13:54,275 --> 00:13:56,844
I know.
I started that rumor.

208
00:13:58,112 --> 00:14:00,715
Well then maybe you should
start looking for someone else.

209
00:14:00,748 --> 00:14:03,851
I can't. I've been crazy about her
since kindergarten,

210
00:14:03,885 --> 00:14:06,854
when I glued my face
to the back of her sweater.

211
00:14:06,888 --> 00:14:09,657
So you've been "stuck on her"
a long time, huh?

212
00:14:09,691 --> 00:14:13,661
But what's the use?
The story never changes.

213
00:14:13,695 --> 00:14:16,498
There's the beautiful princess,
the dashing frog,

214
00:14:16,531 --> 00:14:20,068
and the wart he left behind.

215
00:14:20,101 --> 00:14:23,605
Come on, Screech, I think
you're being too hard on yourself.

216
00:14:31,279 --> 00:14:33,715
<i>Who is it?</i>

217
00:14:34,749 --> 00:14:38,820
- Can I come in?
- Zack?

218
00:14:38,853 --> 00:14:42,190
This is the first time in 11 years
you've come through the door.

219
00:14:42,223 --> 00:14:44,426
Well, there's a special reason.

220
00:14:44,459 --> 00:14:46,661
Here.
These are for you.

221
00:14:46,695 --> 00:14:48,830
Oh, they're beautiful.

222
00:14:48,864 --> 00:14:51,032
We have the same kind
growing in our yard.

223
00:14:52,033 --> 00:14:54,603
Not anymore.

224
00:14:56,138 --> 00:14:58,140
Well, this is just to say thanks
for helping me.

225
00:14:58,173 --> 00:15:01,109
We're not finished yet.
We still have one more lesson.

226
00:15:04,179 --> 00:15:06,515
Pretend I'm Kelly.

227
00:15:06,548 --> 00:15:09,584
"Oh Zack. Help me choose
between you and Slater. "

228
00:15:20,696 --> 00:15:22,698
Voil×!

229
00:15:49,758 --> 00:15:51,961
Lisa, what happened
to you?

230
00:15:51,994 --> 00:15:54,096
I kicked the TV
and sprained my ankle.

231
00:15:54,129 --> 00:15:55,698
Why?

232
00:15:55,731 --> 00:15:59,235
Watching the new Revlon commercial-
they discontinued my nail polish.

233
00:15:59,268 --> 00:16:01,637
That was a dumb thing
to do.

234
00:16:01,670 --> 00:16:04,874
Where were you "Miss Pretty Pants"
when I needed that advice?

235
